#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Docker Installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Preparation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Prepare the host as described below. Before installing any Docker-related "
"packages, you need to enable the container module:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:17
#, no-c-format
msgid "Built-in Docker Orchestration Support"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with Docker 1.12 the container orchestration is now an integral "
"part of the Docker engine. Even though this feature is available in &slsa;"
"SP1 and in &slsa;SP2, it is not supported and it is only a technical "
"preview. Use Kubernetes for Docker containers orchestration, for details "
"refer to the <link xlink:href=\"http://kubernetes.io/docs/getting-started-"
"guides/kubeadm/\">Kubernetes documentation</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling the Container Module Using &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start &yast;, and select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu> "
"Software Repositories</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Add</guimenu> to open the add-on dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <guimenu>Extensions and Modules from Registration Server</guimenu> "
"and click <guimenu>Next</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the list of available extensions and modules, select <guimenu>Container "
"Module 12 x86_64</guimenu> and click <guimenu>Next</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The containers module and its repositories will be added to your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use &smtool;, update the list of repositories on the &smt; server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling the Container Module Using SUSEConnect"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:61
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Container Module can be added also with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_installation.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "$ sudo SUSEConnect -p sle-module-containers/12/x86_64 -r ''"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note about the SUSEConnect syntax"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>-r ''</option> flag is required to avoid a known limitation of "
"SUSEConnect."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing and Setting Up Docker"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install the <systemitem>docker</systemitem> package:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_installation.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo zypper install docker"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "To automatically start the Docker service at boot time:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_installation.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo systemctl enable docker.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "This will automatically enable docker.socket in consequence."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you will use Portus and an SSL secured registry, open the <filename>/"
"etc/sysconfig/docker</filename> file. Search for the parameter "
"<parameter>DOCKER_OPTS</parameter> and add <literal>--insecure-registry "
"<replaceable>ADDRESS_OF_YOUR_REGISTRY</replaceable></literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the production environment when using the SSL secured registry with "
"Portus, add CA certificates to the directory <filename>/etc/docker/certs.d/"
"&lt;registry address&gt;</filename> and copy the CA certificates to your "
"system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_installation.xml:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo cp CA /etc/pki/trust/anchors/ &amp;&amp; update-ca-certificates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the Docker service:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_installation.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo systemctl start docker.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "This will automatically start docker.socket in consequence."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Docker daemon listens on a local socket which is accessible only by the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user and by the members of "
"the <systemitem class=\"groupname\">docker</systemitem> group. The "
"<systemitem class=\"groupname\">docker</systemitem> group is automatically "
"created at package installation time. To allow a certain user to connect to "
"the local Docker daemon, use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_installation.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo /usr/sbin/usermod -aG docker <replaceable>USERNAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The user can communicate with the local Docker daemon upon his next login."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Networking"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want your containers to be able to access the external network, you "
"must enable the <option>ipv4 ip_forward</option> rule. This can be done "
"using &yast; by browsing to <menuchoice> <guimenu>System</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Network Settings</guimenu> <guimenu>Routing</guimenu> </menuchoice> "
"menu and ensuring <option>Enable IPv4 Forwarding</option> is checked."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option cannot be changed when networking is handled by the Network "
"Manager. In such cases the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/SuSEfirewall2</filename> "
"file needs to be edited manually to ensure the <option>FW_ROUTE</option> "
"flag is set to <option>yes</option>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_installation.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "FW_ROUTE=\"yes\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "Networking Limitations on Power Architecture"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently Docker networking has two limitations on the Power architecture."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first limitation is about iptables. &slea;&nbsp;12 machines cannot run "
"Docker with the iptables support enabled. An update of the kernel is going "
"to solve this issue. In the meantime the Docker package for Power has "
"iptables support disabled via a dedicated directive inside of <filename>/etc/"
"sysconfig/docker</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As a result of this limitation Docker containers will not have access to the "
"outer network. A possible workaround is to share the same network namespace "
"between the host and the containers. This however reduces the isolation of "
"the containers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The network namespace of the host can be shared on a per-container basis by "
"adding <option>--net=host</option> to the <option>docker run</option> "
"command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_installation.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid "iptables support on &slea;&nbsp;12 SP1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slea;&nbsp;12 SP1 hosts are not affected by this limitation but, given they "
"use the same &slea;&nbsp;12 package, they will have iptables support "
"disabled. This can be changed by removing the <option>-iptables=false</"
"option> setting inside of <filename>/etc/sysconfig/docker</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_installation.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second limitation is about network isolation between the containers and "
"the host. Currently it is not possible to prevent containers from probing or "
"accessing arbitrary ports of each other."
msgstr ""
